On Mon, 2 Jul 2007, Alan Beck wrote:

> My VW manual says to torque the nuts on the rocker arms of my Type V engine
> to 260 inch pounds from 111 inch pounds.

> I am in the 180's now and I expect something to let go. It is really tight
> and I am afraid to create a big problem.

Are you mistaking inch-pounds for foot-pounds?  260 inch pounds equals a
bit more than 21 foot pounds.  Seems pretty outlandish if you made that
mistake, but just in case...

I always verify torques in more than one manual if I am unsure of what
they should be.
